benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Remove tags from bundle

covered: DELETE operation validated with multiple successful scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04).
Extensive error handling and input validation covered (TC05, TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC13, TC14).
Boundary/edge cases covered (TC04 for no tags, TC12 for large tag sets, TC16 for empty tagDef, TC18 for timeout/large-scale scenarios).
Concurrency and performance considerations addressed (TC15, TC18).
gaps: Pagination: Not applicable for DELETE; no pagination tests are needed for this endpoint.
Rate limiting/throttling tests are missing (no explicit tests for bursts or RATE_LIMIT scenarios).
Caching behavior is not tested (ETag/Cache-Control headers or conditional requests).
Explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios (authenticated but without sufficient permissions) are not present beyond 401 Unauthorized (gap for 403).
Additional edge-case validation around headers and complex error message content could be broadened.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate behavior under bursts of DELETE requests.
Add caching validation tests (ETag/Cache-Control, If-None-Match) and related conditional request handling.
Introduce 403 Forbidden test cases to cover authenticated-but-not-authorized scenarios.
Ensure consistent test data management for large-scale cases (TC12/TC18) to keep test runs repeatable.
Consider expanding header input validation coverage and explicit error-message assertions for all error paths.
